<br>
 Provoke, is being the only useful (and used) anytime style, both in PvE and PvP. When facing high level and epic mobs, Skalds have no other efficient style to use, so they draw aggro and get hit alot with their low defense, which is being lowered by the style itself.<br>
<br>
 Ruiner, having a low to-hit bonus and low damage, is not being used at all.<br>
 <br>
 Comparing 2 provokes to ruiner/crumble: Ruiner chain has a low to-hit opening, and a 2nd style that doesn't compensate. It takes triple endurance than 2 provokes. Crumble has no &quot;proc&quot;, like all other chains. Ruiner chain is MUCH harder to land in RvR.<br>
<br>
 Positionals. Back position has a low to-hit opening, but higher damage than Provoke. On Epic mobs, the **slightly** higher damage doesn't compensate for the miss rate, making Provoke much more useful, which is problematic as I mentioned above. Side positionals are medium on damage and to-hit bonus, but effectively they give the mob a stun immunity.<br>
<br>
 Parry chains. Both of them have bleed effect, which has 2 problems: 1st, as general, only Swords and Axes (slashing weapons) should do bleed. 2nd, Skalds suffer greatly from this, since it gives Mezz immunity for the target. A resisted mezz usually means losing in a 1vs1 fight for us. However, a Skald can use only &quot;Crushing Blow&quot; as a parry-followed, but the idea is to be able to use multiple styles, and not reducing them to 2-4 styles.<br>
<br>
 Snare &quot;proc&quot;. Since a large precent of the Skald's damage is based on it's DD's, they SPECIFICLY shouldn't  break the style's snare. I'd suggest that the snare will be only broken a few seconds after the snared target is being hit by DD. That way, the Skald will be ably to score another snaring hit before it's broken, and it won't give the ability to &quot;kite&quot; the target to death with multiple DD rounds that don't break snare at all.<br>
<br>
Last thing - I personally think it's rather lame that our mezz is broken my a missed hit, and furthermore, that a BACK style on an immobile MEZZED target CAN be missed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qzxmf2>qzxmf2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/3/03 4:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=762.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hem.passagen.se/qzxmf2/head.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Let's discuss styles</span><hr size=1> Id like to see a long duration stun on hammer thats doable to get of as a 2H skald maby parry, x, stun or similar.<br>
