<br>
Assumption:  The most usefull styles for a skald are - in order<br>
1. Anytime<br>
2. Rear Positional<br>
3. Front positional<br>
4. Side positional<br>
5. parry opener<br>
6. evade opener - IMHO not applicable to skalds<br>
7. block opener - IMHO not applicable to skalds<br>
<br>
Style review:<br>
2. Splitter - baby style not used in rvr which is fine<br>
4. CLeave - parry style which is rarely used maybe in 1 on 1 dueling.  The slow effect is nice, but parry is rare in RVR.  the Skald parry chain should lead to a significant stun. Reason being that if a skald is parrying an enemy they should have an opportunity if they land the styles to defend themselves.<br>
6. plague - taunt style -fine<br>
8. Thryms Strength - chains off of Cleave.  a disappointing follow up to cleave. does a tiny bit more dmg then pillager so why bother?  this style should have high dmg and bleed and chain into a final parry style with a stun - maybe raider.<br>
10. Pillager - solid anytime style<br>
12. hoarfrost - detaunt is fine<br>
15. Evernight - behind opener - decent style dmg is ok for an opener.  Bleed could be littel better.<br>
18. plunderer - follow up to anytime style pillager.  Given the ease to get that off this a decent style as is with an attack speed debuff.<br>
21. Valkyeris shield - opens offblock which is USELESS for skald.  I know some skalds (kobolds) use this in pve where we can block occassionally and chain the stun. IMHO this style should be removed for skalds and replaced maybe with a side opener chaining into glacial mvmt with a nice effect.<br>
25. Raider - opens off of evade.  Useless for skalds. THis might be a good spot for 3rd style in parry chain mega dmg no end style.<br>
29. havoc - front positional.  Good style, should lose the defense penalty<br>
34. midnight sun - chains off of block style so its useless.  Also its axe users only stun style. Needs to be changed.<br>
39. Glacial mvmt - side positional. nice style, pointless defense penalty.  There should be more then one in side chain so this might be better spot for a good 2nd style in chain.<br>
44. Artic rift - Follow up to rear style everngiht. ok style but doesnt really outbenefit evernight. They are nearly identical ( one has bleed + med dmg vs high dmg only).  This style is the right spot but could use an effect: stun, proc, snare something<br>
50. Tyrs fury - follow up to front positional havoc.  Not a ton of benefit here cause they are both high dmg styles and the bleed isnt great.<br>
<br>
IMHO Skalds should have access to anytime, front, side, back and parry styles/chains.  Block and evade should not be the opener for any skald styles.<br>
<br>
Anytime styles are easiest so they should be highest end cost and least effective.  Back positionals can be really effective (see annihilation) so evernight chain is important, if anythign this is the style where defensive penalties should be applied.  Side styles are the hardest positionals to land, the axe style deserves more then one of these, this might be the best place for a stun a la savage.  Front styles are usefull but i dont think the 50 styles should be a follow up to a front style. Front styles arent the most used by skalds.  The parry chain could really use help for an axe skald, there might even be grounds for 2 parry chains, 1 defensive/low dmg and 1 offensive/low defense.<br>
<br>
Finally the level 43+ styles for skalds should be really good since battlesongs is sacrificed to get that high.  a 50 skald axe style is the perfect place for a long stun on say a side positional.<br>
