<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bleeds</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Bleed = Mez Immunity and as such is the enemy of a skald who can effectively use his mez in any situation.<br>
<br>
In the Evernight/Arctic Rift Combo, the bleed should be on Arctic Rift and not on Evernight.  As it stands now, I never use the rear styles because of this.  Sure the extra damage would be nice, but not nearly as useful as if I needed to mez my target and move to a different one or mezzing to flee/rest in a 1v1 situation.<br>
<br>
Also, there is currently no reason for a skald to spec to 50 axe.  With the Havoc/Tyr's Fury combo also causing a bleed, the bonus dmg does not outweigh having your target being mezzable.  If you plan on speccing 50 weapon, the choice is currently clear to use Sword.  IMO, Axe needs a solid stun available from one of the style chains other than the Block one.<br>
<br>
<br>
Axe in General (not related specifcally to Skalds) has another issue.<br>
<br>
--The cleave effect does not stack with the Pillager/Plunderer effect.  If you use your anytimes and then use cleave you get a &quot;Target Already Has This Effect&quot; message.<br>
